window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>It was a beautiful story, a perfect romance, and the union of two hearts in the bond of love. Or was it?</p> <p>When J. R. Cobis woke up from his fantasy, he discovered he was living in a nightmare. His once-loving wife had become someone he didn’t recognize. Their marriage flipped the script on domestic violence where the wife was the abuser and the husband was the victim!</p> <p>In this gripping hybrid memoir and self-help audiobook, J. R. Cobis walks you through the gut-wrenching story of his fairy-tale marriage-turned-horror-story in which he discovered that his wife--like so many people--suffered from narcissistic personality disorder among other hidden mental illnesses. He also shares the mechanics of the life of an abused man, detailing how to stay if you choose to stay or how to leave when staying is impossible.</p> <p>He covers:</p> <ul> <li>How to identify the subtle signs of mental disorder in the woman you love</li> <li>How to protect your children, home, and finances from an abusive partner</li> <li>How to maneuver the tricky legal system</li> <li>How to safeguard your job and reputation from a vindictive abuser</li> <li>How to apply the lessons learned from the Johnny Depp v. Amber Heard trial</li> <li>And so much more!</li> </ul> <p><i>No Wrath Like a Woman’s</i> will challenge you as J. R. Cobis unfolds his journey and explains how he handled the issue of female abuse, which is growing more and more common. You will also be informed so you can protect yourself, your children, and the life you have built.</p>"; 
